==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lignin
<hw>Lig"nin</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g"n⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lignum</ets> wood: cf. F. <ets>lignine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A substance characterizing wood cells and
differing from cellulose in its conduct with certain chemical
reagents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Recent authors have distinguished four forms of this
substance, naming them <xex>lignose</xex>, <xex>lignin</xex>,
<xex>lignone</xex>, and <xex>lignireose</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligniperdous</ent>⟦br⟧
